|text1     = The {{Color|h|nobold=1|Chrono Vessel}} is a temporal ritual tool crafted by Oronyx's priests, with various sizes and styles. {{Color|h|nobold=1|Breaking}} the Chrono Vessel will {{Color|h|nobold=1|pause time in the area around it.}}
|image2    = Tutorial Oronyx's Prayer Chrono Vessel and Time Stop 2.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_635002.png>-<Tutorial Oronyx's Prayer Chrono Vessel and Time Stop 2.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text2     = When facing a broken Chrono Vessel, {{Color|h|nobold=1|rewinding it will fix the vessel}} and allow time to flow again in the surrounding area.
|image3    = Tutorial Oronyx's Prayer Chrono Vessel and Time Stop 3.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_635003.png>-<Tutorial Oronyx's Prayer Chrono Vessel and Time Stop 3.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text3     = While {{Color|h|nobold=1|rewinding}} an object, that object {{Color|h|nobold=1|will not be affected by the time-stopped zone.}}
|image4    = Tutorial Oronyx's Prayer Chrono Vessel and Time Stop 4.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_635004.png>-<Tutorial Oronyx's Prayer Chrono Vessel and Time Stop 4.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text4     = If you wish to {{Color|h|nobold=1|freeze a moving object at a specific time,}} you can pre-emptively {{Color|h|nobold=1|deploy a Time Stop Zone}}, then {{Color|h|nobold=1|initiate Rewind,}} and {{Color|h|nobold=1|manually interrupt the Rewind}} at the desired moment.
|image5    = Tutorial Oronyx's Prayer Chrono Vessel and Time Stop 5.png{{subst:void|<!--$UPLOAD:<<SpriteOutput/TutorialPic/TutorialPage_633301.png>-<Tutorial Oronyx's Prayer Chrono Vessel and Time Stop 5.png>-<Tutorial Files>>-->}}
|text5     = Hint: Some characters' Techniques can also trigger Time Stop, such as {{Color|h|nobold=1|Trailblazer (Path of Remembrance)}} and others.
